{"id":21872,"title":"Quantification of salt-induced changes in Root System Architecture in Arabidopsis","title_html":"Quantification of salt-induced changes in Root System Architecture in Arabidopsis","image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/be5eg3kw.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/be5eg3kw.jpg"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.zkqf4vw","doi_status":2,"uri":"quantification-of-salt-induced-changes-in-root-sys-zkqf4vw","type_id":1,"published_on":1553779312,"version_id":0,"created_on":1553776487,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"Magdalena Julkowska","affiliation":"King Abdullah University of Science and Technology","username":"magdalena-julkowska","link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/pr-journal.s3.amazonaws.com\/vrfg3kw.jpeg","placeholder":"https:\/\/pr-journal.s3.amazonaws.com\/vrfg3kw.jpeg"},"badges":[{"id":4,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/gold.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/gold.svg"},"name":"Gold power author!"}],"research_interests":null},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":9,"authors":[{"name":"Magdalena Julkowska","affiliation":"King Abdullah University of Science and Technology","username":"magdalena-julkowska","link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/pr-journal.s3.amazonaws.com\/vrfg3kw.jpeg","placeholder":"https:\/\/pr-journal.s3.amazonaws.com\/vrfg3kw.jpeg"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},{"name":"Christa Testerink","affiliation":"Wageningen University, University of Amsterdam, ","username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"research_interests":null}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":0,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":0,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"steps":[{"id":725639,"guid":"1FCEA160515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B0CCAD9D729B4779A01A104FE0830948","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4C5D1B6855434E45B947CEB628E16AD1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare germination media.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Per 1L of media: 2.2 g Murashi-Skoog, 5 g sucrose, 1 g MES Monohydrate, pH at 5.8 with KOH. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">After adjusting the pH add 10g Dashin agar directly into the bottle. Make sure you add it AFTER measuring pH - it can clog the pH meter otherwise.Autoclave using liquid sterilization cycle.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Pour 40 ml per square plate (12x12cm) and let it dry in the laminar hood for at least one hour (can be up to three hours) - long drying time will reduce the condensation at the plate surface.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Put the plates (still in the laminar hood) in the plastic bags that they came in - put the tape to close the plastic bags and write your name & date => store at 4C<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":725640,"guid":"1FDDBC90515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":725639,"previous_guid":"1FCEA160515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7C5A5AD9EC864D1F87E96135ADACAF83","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"438C9F2D36B84C7FBA421989E1437F04","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Sterilize the seeds.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Soak the seeds in 50% Bleach (50% from the original household bottle - diluted in 1:1 ratio with MQ) for 10 minutes - DON'T vortex but gently shake once in a while.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer the work into the laminar hoodWash the seeds with sterile MQ using 1ml pipette 5-8 times.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">After sterilization - store the seeds in the 4C for overnight to ensure equal germination.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">NOTE: Do not store the seeds at 4C for longer than a week - after that, they start to germinate in the dark and you end up with etiolated seedlings - NOT good for the experiment<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":725641,"guid":"1FDDE3A0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":725640,"previous_guid":"1FDDBC90515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9958C36962FA4A418F294BCC4F0CA9C7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"747B64DBF83046088D08B0781C57D9D7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Put the seeds on the plate (approximately 150-200 seeds per plate)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Get the seeds from 4C and transfer both the 1\/2 MS agar plates and the seeds into a cleaned laminar hood.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Use the pipette with the manual control of volume (the ring) and suck the seed \u201csuspension\u201d into the 1ml pipette tip (STERILE!)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">In the laminar hood - put the seeds onto the plate by gently touching the plate surface with the pipette tip - if they are not coming out - reduce the volume while touching the plate surfaceLet the plates dry in the laminar hood until all the water droplets evaporate - put the agar plates on the top of the plate lid for 5 minutes<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Close the plates and wrap the plate ende using the leukopor tape.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":725642,"guid":"1FDE0AB0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":725641,"previous_guid":"1FDDE3A0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1311DE06701247E2AAC8DB1D11398BBB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2B1139D1C43E43E09CBA7BD2B69FD5D4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Put in the plates in the growth chamber <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">usually, we grow the plates under +\/- 70 degrees angle stacked in a ribbed tray used as a bottom for normal plant pots. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Let the seeds germinate in the growth chamber set at 16h light, 8h dark, 22C and 60% humidity.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":725643,"guid":"1FDE31C0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":725642,"previous_guid":"1FDE0AB0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EE8F5ADC91FD4CBDBA4D6AC8EC88B5C9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"EC2F102B0E024B7BA3030BDA83DC9F4A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare the \u201ctreatment\u201d plates:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Use the basic media concentration as described above - but now add salt - make media containing 0, 75 and 125 mM NaCl (added after pH measurement - pH should be ok because of the MES buffer).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Pour the plates according to the instructions above and let dry in the laminar hood between 1 and 3 hours.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":725644,"guid":"1FDE31C1515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":725643,"previous_guid":"1FDE31C0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F5F487C4D1A64C0483C4F4B3EA014527","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"975BFDABB15C46508A11DEF1370807F5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Four days after germination (usually - I put the plates in the growth chamber for germination on Thursday and transfer on Monday) - transfer the germinated seedlings to new plates containing 0\/75\/125 mM NaCl<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Usually, we aim to have at least 12 replicas per condition per genotype. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer the seedlings with sterile (or freshly opened) yellow pipette tips.Seal the plates with leukopor tape.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Each plate gets divided into two halves - and each half will contain 2 seedlings of each genotype. Please see the picture below:<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/be5kg3kw.jpg\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"C7D325158C5C4D0989ACB2263248FBFB","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/be5kg3kw.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":725645,"guid":"1FDE58D0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":725644,"previous_guid":"1FDE31C1515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"70EF7F4A0CF443B9B23EEA5642891D2D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E656F45F1F7145C2878E2005A6F85A69","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Put a dot with a permanent marker to mark the position of main root tip \/ scan the plates before putting them back into the growth chamber \/ Percival<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":725646,"guid":"1FDE58D1515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":725645,"previous_guid":"1FDE58D0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"681398E61FE045F1A75F40146D46B5DE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1642837F021345AAACD80216104951BA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Scan the plates every two days until the plants are 12 days old (or whenever the root architecture becomes too complex). Scan the plates at 200 dpi resolution - this will optimize the file size and still allow you to identify the emerging lateral roots. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">IMPORTANT - make sure to scan the plants with the black background.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null},{"id":725647,"guid":"1FDE7FE0515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","previous_id":725646,"previous_guid":"1FDE58D1515B11E994E85FDE75D4DEF7","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E32A6A10E93A47A2B2EAF5C2D6CA9509","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"79AC7A2298DB4FA98E650CD922C99063","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Analyze the root system architecture using the <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Smart Root<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> or <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">EZ-Rhizo (windows only)<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null}],"materials":[{"id":343,"mol_weight":56.11,"name":"Potassium hydroxide","linfor":"KOH","url":"http:\/\/store.p212121.com\/potassium-hydroxide-pellets\/?utm_source=zappylab.benchtools&utm_medium=ios&utm_campaign=p21nov13","sku":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"P212121","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/store.p212121.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/7.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/7.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":7},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":3336,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Murashige & Skoog medium including B5 vitamins","linfor":null,"url":"","sku":"M0231","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Duchefa Biochemie","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.duchefa-biochemie.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":109},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":48242,"mol_weight":0,"name":"MES, free acid, monohydrate","linfor":null,"url":"https:\/\/www.biobasic.com\/us\/mes-free-acid-monohydrate-4311","sku":"MB0341.SIZE.25g","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Bio Basic Inc.","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/biobasic.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":120},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":116689,"mol_weight":58.44,"name":"Sodium Chloride","linfor":"ClNa","url":"https:\/\/www.fishersci.com\/shop\/products\/sodium-chloride-crystalline-certified-acs-fisher-chemical-6\/p-33727","sku":"S271-3","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Fisher Scientific","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.fishersci.com\/us\/en\/home.html","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":31},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":119261,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Sucrose","linfor":null,"url":"","sku":"S7903","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Sigma Aldrich","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/sigmaaldrich.com","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":17},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":125360,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Daishin agar","linfor":null,"url":"","sku":"9002-18-0","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Duchefa Biochemie","affiliation":null,"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.duchefa-biochemie.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"id":109},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The protocol was developed for observing salt-induced changes in Root System Architecture of Arabidopsis and other small plants. The seeds are germinated in control conditions, and exposed to stress 4 days after germination. As the agar plates are transparent, this system provides quick, easy and non-destructive method to observe development of roots. This protocol was used to produced the data in two manuscripts from our lab - <\/span><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Julkowska et al., 2014 Plant Physiology<\/span><\/a><span> and <\/span><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Julkowska et al., 2017 Plant Cell<\/span><\/a><span>. <\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1553779312}